    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Meshalkin Research Institute of Pathology of Circulation</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this prospective randomized study was to assess the efficacy of ablation of the
      ganglionated plexi localized in the epicardial fat pads for preventing recurrences of atrial
      tachyarrhythmia in patients with paroxysmal atrial fibrillation undergoing coronary artery
      bypass grafting.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
